  m_text: Also known as the Law of Ellipses, it states that all orbital paths of
    planets take on an elliptical shape, with the Sun as one of its focus. If we
    are to recall our geometry, an ellipse is a conic section wherein it has foci
    located in its semi- major axis. You can check the diagram.
